Business Brief -- LTV Corp.:
   Aerospace and Defense Unit
   Wins $700 Million Contract
The contract calls for the aerospace unit to continue to
make tail sections and vertical and horizontal stabilizers
for the 747, vertical and horizontal stabilizers for the 757
and horizontal stabilizers for the 767.
   As part of its bankruptcy reorganization plan, LTV has
agreed to sell its aircraft and missile businesses for $355
million to a new company, Vought Corp., that will be jointly
owned by Lockheed Corp. and Martin Marietta Corp. That
transaction is still subject to bankruptcy court approval.